<br>
<br>
<b>"The Backbreaker"</b><br>
Situation to be used: 1vs1 mainly.<br>
Requirements: Hammer Skill up to "Sledgehammer" Level. Mousemovement is an advantage.<br>
<br>
You are running towards that RR5+ Opponent who has probably purge and you won't be able to kite him. He probably get's into "Stickmode" just before reaching you an prepares to do his opening style.<br>
Wait till he's right in front of you, fire your two dds, then your mezz and run straight through him. Turn 180 degree instantly and while he fumbles for his Purge button hit him with your conquerer. Your mezz just ruined his opening and if you use the mouse to turn, you are most of the times turning much to fast for him to prevent the backstyle. Do your Sledgehammer next and you do major damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>"Pursuit Charges"</b><br>
Situation to be used: You are pursuing a healer/caster/songclass who is running around to get rid of you.<br>
Requirements: DoT Charges<br>
<br>
We all know it the situation. You encountered the enemy group, picked that druid but he starts to run in circles and you miss time after time. Or you've been snared. Or you don't have any endurance left, or he's got interlaced PBT - whatever.<br>
<br>
Just put your weapon away and use those neat DoT Charges! (I have 10 of them on my boots). I can't count the numerous occasions I have used those and prevented the guy in front of me from casting and finally killed him.<br>
<br>
<br>
I would appreciate your input... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aurensirramalot>AurenSirRamAlot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Auren/fullsize/shield.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/26/03 6:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=611.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald RvR Tactics</span><hr size=1> instead of using mouse to move when your un through him. use the face button, bound to a key on your keyboard.<br>
